Your challenge

ClusterHQ needs you to help establish QA for next generation cloud software, in the new domain of containerisation.

Your role

This is chance to be part of something new, where you can have a voice and be recognised for helping produce disruptive open source container software that will impact infrastructure, application architecture and software delivery as fundamentally in the coming years as virtualisation has in the last decade. 

Joining as our first Lead QA Engineer, we welcome your ability to establish and run a robust QA function as a service, building on the foundations that are serving us well. You’ll have our full support in running good process, getting the most from our tooling and achieving best practice in TDD.

Your work will pave the way for other QA colleagues to join you, each dedicated to a product engineering SCRUM team. We will look to you as we hire new team members, as we plan their work, get them up to speed and expand our operation. 

ClusterHQ is offering relocation to Bristol, UK, which is fast becoming the cloud computing hub of Europe and is renowned for its high quality of life.

About you

•	You have established and run QA for a software product or comprehensive feature set
•	You are skilled at testing in a technical, system-level, domain e.g. networking, clustering, storage, operating system, middleware, cloud platforms, virtualisation, clustering, microservices, orchestration or containerisation
•	You can define and implement QA strategies and plans for functional and non-functional testing, e.g. security, integration, performance, scalability
•	You can identify and implement automated testing approaches using modern frameworks and tools
•	You enjoy a multi skilled role - running tests and resolving issues, and recording, interpreting and presenting results
•	You can produce effective test scripts, using languages such as Python, Ruby, Perl, C++, Tcl, Groovy etc.

Salary and benefits

•	Competitive joining salary
•	Equity in a fast growing company
•	Discretionary relocation assistance
•	Flexible working | 28 days holiday + public holidays | pension | death in service | income protection | private healthcare | dental care | Cyclescheme | good coffee | on site restaurant

About us - ClusterHQ

ClusterHQ is a newly funded open source software provider, front and centre of the containerisation world. With five years in R&D and substantial funding from Accel Partners, we’ve just released our first product, Flocker, supporting the Docker ecosystem. Effective software design is at the heart of our organisation and fundamental to our future. Our global team includes accomplished open source contributors on projects such as Twisted and OpenZFS. We invite you to join our world class engineering teams. https://clusterhq.com/careers/

Located: central Bristol, near Temple Meads station

